adams.flow.control.Flow
	-annotation
	In this flow, the ability to attach global actors to options is demonstrated.\nThe For-Loop runs from 1 to 10 and the current loop value is stored in\nthe variable \"i\". The variable \"val\", initialized with \"0\", is then incremented\nby the value that the global actor \"increment\" generates (in our case, the\nvalue of \"i\" times 2).
	-actor
		adams.flow.standalone.SetVariable
			-name
			SetVariable-1
			-var-name
			val
			-var-value
			0
	-actor
		adams.flow.standalone.CallableActors
			-actor
				adams.flow.source.SequenceSource
					-name
					increment
					-actor
						adams.flow.source.Variable
							-var-name
							i
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.Convert
							-conversion
								adams.data.conversion.StringToInt
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.MathExpression
							-expression
							X*2
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.Convert
							-name
							Convert-1
							-conversion
								adams.data.conversion.DoubleToInt
	-actor
		adams.flow.source.ForLoop
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.SetVariable
			-var-name
			i
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.IncVariable
			-var-name
			val
			-inc-int
			@{callable:increment}
	-actor
		adams.flow.control.Trigger
			-tee
				adams.flow.source.Variable
					-var-name
					val
			-tee
				adams.flow.sink.Display
					-writer
						adams.data.io.output.NullWriter
	-flow-execution-listener
		adams.flow.execution.NullListener

